To add the script as a command:

navigate to the script folder and type: mv scriptname.sh scriptname ( remove the .sh extension to use it as a normal command )

For the current bash session:
PATH=$PATH:script_path

For permanently using the command (even after rebooting):

cd
vi .bashrc 

################################################################
to edit in vi type i and start editing 
to save and close press Esc and the colon followed by x (:x)
at the end of the .bashrc file add the following:
export PATH=$PATH:script_path
################################################################
then type the following in the terminal after saving the changes:

source .bashrc
################################################################
Have a great day :D
